Class Matchers

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.roscopeco.moxy.matchers.Matchers
  • public class Matchers
extends Object

    Provides static access to the standard Moxy argument matchers.

    This class, along with the Moxy class, are the main top-level classes most users will need to interact with when using Moxy. They are designed so you can simply import static and start mocking.

    The methods in this class should only be called in the context of a Moxy when(...) or assertMock(...) call. Calling them out of context will result in InconsistentMatchersException or PossibleMatcherUsageError exceptions when interacting with the framework.

    For a mini example, see Moxy. For full details, see README.md.

    Note: Many of the standard matchers provided with this class come in both primitive and reference versions. It is important that you use the appropriate primitive type if the method matchers are applied to expects primitive arguments. See README for more details.
